===Noun===
'''platypus''' (plural: '''platypuses''')

# An egg-laying, semiaquatic mammal with a bill like that of a [[duck]], a tail like that of a [[beaver]], a waterproof pelt, and (in males) flat webbed feet with poisonous spurs on the inside of the back legs.  The platypus, ([[Ornithorhynchus]] [[anatinus]]) lives in the freshwater streams of Tasmania and eastern Australia.

